      • onCrossBoundary

        public boolean onCrossBoundary(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                               org.bukkit.Location from,
                               org.bukkit.Location to,
                               ApplicableRegionSet toSet,
                               Set<ProtectedRegion> entered,
                               Set<ProtectedRegion> exited,
                               MoveType moveType)
        Description copied from class: Handler
        Called when a player has moved into a new location where either there are fewer regions or more regions.

        This is called only if the move test (Session.testMoveTo(Player, Location, MoveType)) was successful.

        If this method returns false, then no other handlers will be run (for this move attempt).

        Overrides:
        onCrossBoundary in class Handler
        Parameters:
        player - The player
        from - The previous, valid, location
        to - The new location to test
        toSet - The regions for the new location
        entered - The list of regions that have been entered
        exited - The list of regions that have been left
        moveType - The type of move
        Returns:
        Whether the movement should be allowed
